text: William II (27 May 1626 â€“ 6 November 1650) was sovereign Prince of Orange and Stadtholder of Holland, Zeeland, Utrecht, Guelders, Overijssel and Groningen in the United Provinces of the Netherlands from 14 March 1647 until his death three years later. His only child, William III, reigned as King of England, Ireland, and Scotland. ==References== Category:1626 births Category:1650 deaths Category:Heads of state Category:House of Orange-Nassau
